<subSubSection pageId="17" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="17.[707,1193,991,1065]" pageId="17">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[731,845,991,1012]" pageId="17">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet is a Latin adjective that stems from 
<emphasis box="[899,957,1017,1038]" italics="true" pageId="17">macer</emphasis>
(= thin) and refers to the narrow shape of the antennal capitulum.
</paragraph>
